\b Security Operations Assessment Workbook\b0\par
\par
Assigned controls: AU-2 Event Logging and SI-4 System Monitoring.\par
Primary teams: Security Operations, SOC, Detection Engineering, SRE.\par
\par
\b AU-2 Event Logging\b0\par
Objective: Define and maintain the event types the system can log and those the organization requires to log for investigations and monitoring.\par
\par
1. Log-capable event types are identified.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
2. Logging requirements are coordinated with stakeholders.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
3. Required event types and logging conditions are defined.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
4. Rationale exists for why selected events support investigations.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
5. Logged event types are reviewed and updated on schedule.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
\par
Evidence requests: logging standard, event catalog, log source inventory, rationale mapping, review records, sample logs.\par
Repo gap note: Logging is primarily console-based with no structured audit log standard visible.\par
\par
\b SI-4 System Monitoring\b0\par
Objective: Monitor systems for attacks, indicators of attack, unauthorized connections, and anomalies, and provide actionable monitoring information.\par
\par
1. Monitoring objectives are defined.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
2. The system monitors for attacks and indicators of attacks.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
3. The system monitors for unauthorized local, network, and remote connections.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
4. Unauthorized use is identified using defined methods.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
5. Monitoring capabilities are strategically placed to collect essential information.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
6. Monitoring can be deployed ad hoc for transactions of interest.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
7. Detected events and anomalies are analyzed.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
8. Monitoring activity is adjusted when risk changes.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
9. Legal review of monitoring activities is obtained.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
10. Monitoring information is provided to defined roles on a defined basis.\par
Status: ____________________  Evidence: ____________________\par
Notes: ________________________________________________________________\par
\par
Evidence requests: monitoring strategy, SIEM or IDS configuration, alert catalog, event review evidence, tuning records, legal or privacy review, monitoring reports.\par
Repo gap note: No telemetry instrumentation or monitoring integration is visible in application code.\par
\par
\b Baseline Focus\b0\par
Low impact: AU-2 base only; SI-4 base only.\par
Moderate impact: AU-2 base only; SI-4 includes SI-4(2), (4), (5).\par
